|YKOAfter many warning shouts and messages I am going to formally
post about the use of clients for scripting aka client-side
scripting. Use of in-game scripting is allowed.

|YKBTHIS ONLY APPLIES TO CLIENT-SIDE SCRIPTING.

|CKODefinition
|WKO----------

|YKOIn the eyes of the admin a script is the use of some sort of
terminal assistance program/code that will allow the user
of DW to execute multiple mud commands that require multiple
<enter>'s with just one command and <enter> by the user of the
terminal program.  Scripts do not include guild abilities or
the built in scripting ability of the mud.

|CKOBuilt-in Scripting
|WKO------------------

|YKOThe built in |CKBscript|YKO command may be used to run short,
comma-separated command lists. It also supports pacing a command with
|CKBdelay <seconds> <command>|YKO or |CKBdelay <seconds>s <command>|YKO,
such as:

  |CKBscript look,delay 5s north,look

Each delayed step may wait up to 60 seconds, and a single script may
contain up to 300 total seconds of delay.

Global emotes and guild emotes currently available to your character may be
used as script steps. A guild emote becomes invalid immediately if you leave
that guild or its abilities become inactive.

|CKOExamples
|WKO--------

|YKOThe following are examples of what we consider scripting.  This
is in no way an all inclusive list.

 |BKB- |CKBUsing a command such as 5e in a client program to move you
   5 square east by means of only hitting 1 button.

 |BKB- |CKBA single command that will burn a corpse and take everything that
   was on the corpse.

 |BKB- |CKBA single command that will take you from for example COT to
   hyper.
   
 |BKB- |CKBA single command that will log you in, buy kegs/meals, get
   a pony, take you to an area, and begin killing.

|CKOJustification
|WKO-------------

|YKOEveryone here hates lag.  Scripts are the major causes of LAG here
on DW.  Some may ask how a script causes lag.  Remember that the
mud can execute only one command at a time.  When a player has a 
computer enter multiple commands as fast as the computer can these
commands get queued up in the driver until they are executed.  These
commands get issued faster than the mud can process them.  When 
multiple people use scripts the queue grows larger and larger until
the mud's driver can catch up with it.  To the normal user, this
person must wait until his turn in the queue get issued.  Hence,
to this person is a sense of lag.

|CKOPunishment
|WKO----------

|YKOCurrently the punishment for the first offense in the the use of
scripting as determined by nthe admin of DW is loss of 1 lvl, 1 
of each stat, and twice as much exp has the player has on hand.  
This may change to half the players levels, half the stats, and
twice the EXP on hand.  Repeated offenses will be dealt with
by banishment.  Such punishment can be dealt as deemed necessary
by the admin of DW.

|CKOConclusion
|WKO----------

|YKOPlease do not ruin the fun of all on DW with scripting.  All it
does is ruin the fun for us all.  The administration of Darkwind
also frowns upon the use of clients which are capable of executing
scripts, for obvious reasons.
